President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These individuals will serve on the President's Advisory Council on Financial Capability, which aims to improve financial literacy and promote beneficial financial products and services for consumers. The Council will provide advice to the President on financial education efforts, promoting understanding of financial products and services, and more. The appointments include John W. Rogers, Jr. as Chair, Lorraine Cole as Vice Chair, and several other members with diverse backgrounds and expertise in finance and education. This Council is part of President Obama's commitment to promote financial capability and protect consumers, which includes the creation of the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau.